      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That makes sense, but it's more than just variance. When I look at the raw logs, it looks like the model is almost intentionally assigning lower weights to candidates who have very standard, linear career paths, while boosting people with unconventional or \"patchy\" histories. It’s like there’s a hidden metric being used that isn't in the documentation. Can you provide a technical breakdown of what's actually driving those specific boosts?",
